Her problem was already solved.

28:42.013 --> 28:44.846
She wanted to help women
who were still in bad relationships.

28:45.057 --> 28:47.844
-Wanted to help other women end them.
-Works in Accounting.

28:48.060 --> 28:51.018
Gives her access to the names
of every woman who got assistance.

28:51.188 --> 28:53.440
Perfect opportunity
to identify violent spouses.

28:53.649 --> 28:55.480
-Target-rich environment.
-I'm on my way.

28:55.693 --> 28:58.150
Get a BOLO out on all vehicles
registered to Tracy.

28:58.362 --> 29:01.695
We got a code nine. Deploy
every available unit to her address.

29:01.908 --> 29:04.194
I don't want to do this, but I have to.

29:04.410 --> 29:06.651
Nobody can connect me to Mary
butyou.

29:06.871 --> 29:10.705
ME won't buy it. Victimology's all wrong.
The Deer Hunter killed men.

29:11.709 --> 29:13.324
Is that what you call them? Men?

29:13.753 --> 29:16.369
This wasn't supposed to happen
this way.

29:16.923 --> 29:19.630
I didn't want to hurt Mary
or anybody else.

29:19.842 --> 29:20.957
Anybody but them.

29:22.136 --> 29:23.251
I understand.

29:23.721 --> 29:26.258
-Maybe a jury will.
-That's what I said.

29:27.808 --> 29:30.094
To the Deer Hunter, the real one.

29:30.311 --> 29:31.801
He was my husband.

29:33.272 --> 29:37.060
My God. His father was a bastard.

29:37.777 --> 29:41.645
Pushing him, pushing him,
picking on him, cutting him down.

29:41.864 --> 29:45.982
He didn't want to face what he was,
so he overcompensated.

29:46.786 --> 29:48.242
Always pretending.

29:49.330 --> 29:51.491
Macho, tough.

29:53.334 --> 29:55.950
Trying too hard with the ladies,
but I knew.

29:56.170 --> 29:59.628
After we got married, there's--
There's nothing that can hide that.

30:01.509 --> 30:05.843
You'd think that after his father died,
that he'd come to grips with it.

30:06.597 --> 30:10.465
He got angry, mean, isolated.

30:10.685 --> 30:13.802
Every weekend on hunting trips.
That's what he called them.

30:15.272 --> 30:16.307
You had no idea.

30:17.608 --> 30:21.476
After the separation,
I was staying at my sister's.

30:21.696 --> 30:24.153
I came by the house one night
to get my things.

30:24.365 --> 30:26.981
I thought he was gone,
but he was in here, in the garage.

30:27.201 --> 30:29.613
He had blood on his mouth,
on his clothes.

30:30.621 --> 30:35.581
The Deer Hunter had been
all over the news.

30:35.960 --> 30:40.795
So in that moment,
I knew what he'd done.

30:41.007 --> 30:43.589
And I tried to leave, but....

30:44.260 --> 30:45.545
But he came towards me.

30:46.554 --> 30:49.011
He knew I knew
so he couldn't let me go.

30:49.974 --> 30:52.215
And I'd never held a weapon.

30:54.770 --> 30:58.058
I'd fended him off with a knife before,
but that?

30:58.274 --> 30:59.389
I never held a bow.

30:59.608 --> 31:02.771
Before I knew it, the arrow
went straight through his heart.

31:09.035 --> 31:11.117
You could continue.

31:11.412 --> 31:12.492
You could....

31:12.705 --> 31:14.070
Well, yeah.

31:14.290 --> 31:17.828
All those women Whitehaven had helped,
just like me.

31:18.252 --> 31:21.915
I could give them their lives back
by becoming him.

31:22.131 --> 31:24.918
And it's not easy. It's hard work.

31:25.134 --> 31:28.592
It's filthy work, but it's worth it.

31:30.473 --> 31:33.931
Just to he-- Just to see them scared
for a change...

31:34.143 --> 31:37.431
...to hear them whimper and....

31:37.813 --> 31:40.555
And-- And beg.

31:42.234 --> 31:43.770
